history.text: I love this movie! Have you seen it?
I have! and I recently made my bf watch it too because he hasn't seen it, and he also loved it!
Which character is your favorite?
hahah I love it! So quotable the more people that know the better
For sure Janis Ian I love that she is the mastermind behind all the pranks on Regina
What about you?
haha yes, I was going to say her too!
I always forget that Tina Fey directed this. I love her scenes and the teacher
I think it has a really great message too!
She is hilarious and so empowering for girls worldwide
What do you think the message of the movie is?
That talking bad about other people doesn't do any one good
It makes you feel better in the moment but in the long run its not worth it
I agree
Plus a really funny movie

Wow, and I didn't know it was based on a non-fiction self-help book. That makes a lot 
of sense!
Do you think Lindsey Lohan is a good actress?
I totally forgot her parents were zoologists
Yeah I think this is one of her best movies! But I still think parent trap is the best
what is your favorite scene in the movie?
I think it's really funny when they are in the cafeteria and they all turn into animal personalities. I believe it is in the beginning of the movie when Lohan is walking in for the first time.
What about yours?
I like that part too! My favorite is after Regina gets hits by the bus and Cady realize all the bad things she done and has to make peace with everyone
Do you usually watch high school movies like this"
Not actively, I saw the movie because I heard it was really good. Especially since I am older now I don't really like watching movies about highschool kids
Do you think this accurately depicts the typical high school experience?
Oh and I do love the scene when she wins prom queen and breaks apart her tiara lol

I like when her dad lets her out of the house even
 though she is grounded
I think it does reflect what high school is about. In my high school days I was definatly like Janis. And there is sually a click of cheerleaders
High school in general is very clicky. So I think this is a good moive because it teaches you to be more accepting of others you don't know about
Really? There were people that ran the school like that?
